summary: Leg day on Metallicadpa's PPL via /r/Fitness
title: Leg day on Metallicadpa's PPL via /r/Fitness
body:
Hi,

Due to injuries, I can’t do too much back squats right now, so for Metallicadpa’s I was thinking of switching from this :

2x5, 1x5+ squat

3x8-12 Romanian Deadlift

3x8-12 leg press

3x8-12 leg curls

5x8-12 calf raises

​

To this :

2x5, 1x5+ Front Squats

3x8-12 Romanian Deadlift

3x8-12 leg press

3x8-12 leg curls

3x8-12 Thigh Adductor (recommended by therapist)

5x8-12 calf raises

​

As you can see, I switched Squats for Front Squats, would that be too much quad work ?

What do you think ?

​

Thanks a lot

via reddit http://bit.ly/2FN4JCH

summary: So my friend, who is also losing weight, asked what my goal weight is and I was like I don't really know. I've never been under...
body:
So my friend, who is also losing weight, asked what my goal weight is and I was like I don’t really know. I’ve never been under 150 but I’m thinking in the 130s. And she was going on about how that’s so small, even 150 is small. I don’t think thats an unreasonable goal for myself. I’m 5’ 5" and 130s seems like a healthy weight for that height.

On another note, I weighed in this morning and I’m now in the 170s! Whoop!
